cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image classification using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these networks in autonomous underwater vehicles, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also proposes new modules for the neural networks, which could potentially fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the computational performance of the networks, which could fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
